programme.title: Wild At Heart

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The chopper team has an intense struggle to keep a young Waikato woman alive after her car collided with a heavy truck, an 18 year old man is in terrible pain with a dislocated shoulder, and a 9 year old boy is in a bad way after falling out of a tree.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 65-year old Dave, a surf skier, is attacked and bitten by a Great White shark while training in the ocean. Dehydrated (after four days at sea), Margo needs urgent hospital care.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: The Westpac chopper crew attempt to save a Waiheke man who has life-threatening injuries after falling off a ladder and a motocross rider is in a bad way after a 100-foot jump goes badly wrong.

programme.title: On Tour: Stockcar Race

programme.title: On Tour: Air Show

programme.title: On Tour: XCC Finale Triptis

programme.title: On Tour: Snow Mobiles

programme.title: On Tour: Boat Show Duesseldorf

programme.title: On Tour: Kings of Xtreme

programme.title: On Tour: Snow & Ice Drifting

programme.desc: A young woman named Kristy has been haunted in her own bedroom since she can remember. Now it's up to Ryan and the crew to help Kristy before she's overwhelmed by the entity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Knickerbocker
programme.desc: PRS checks into the Knickerbocker Hotel in Linesville, Pennsylvania where the owners are reporting strange noises and the appearance of phantom children in some of the rooms.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Beer, Wine and Spirits
programme.desc: Brian's bar has a cranky customer who's got a bad habit of breaking wine glasses. Charlie has been dead since prohibition.

programme.title: Paranormal State: If I Should Die...
programme.desc: Proven paranormal investigator Ken Arrington leads a new class of characters as they try to help a family cope with what appears to be a demonic spirit in their home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Invitation to Evil
programme.desc: Paula and her husband Mike are under siege by a purported shadow demon in their North Carolina home. Paula has witnessed a toddler bed levitating and heard deep growls. Michelle, Ryan and the team uncover the shocking truth behind the haunting.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dark Man
programme.desc: A grieving mother suspects her deceased son may have fallen victim to a mysterious entity called The Dark Man.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vegas
programme.desc: The PRS travels to Sin City to investigate a 14-year old medium who claims to speak to a dead girl.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Cemetery
programme.desc: PRS visits a gothic graveyard, where a jealous spirit seems to be preying on the newlywed wife of the cemetery's caretaker. Ryan traces the haunting to a mysterious, unclaimed cremation urn on the grounds.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Fire
programme.desc: Christina has been experiencing paranormal activity ever since her father and step-mother were murdered near Columbus, OH last year. PRS and psychic/medium?Chip Coffey delve into a open murder case and wind up exposing a family divide.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Good Vs. Evil
programme.desc: PRS visits a western Pennsylvania couple wracked by a torrent of paranormal activity.

programme.title: Most Haunted: RAF East Kirkby
programme.desc: The "Most Haunted" team visits the Lincolnshire Aviation Heritage Centre. There, they investigate reports of ghostly pilots who have returned after being killed during World War II.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Edinburgh Vaults
programme.desc: The 19 arches beneath Edinburgh's South Bridge were turned into underground vaults housing unsavory characters. Body snatchers Burke and Hare are believed to have operated there. The team investigates.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Leith Hall
programme.desc: Murders, strange noises and an apparition of a wounded soldier take the team to Leith Hall. Grey mists, eerie music and the spectral image of a white lady all lie in wait for the "Most Haunted" team.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Aberglasney House
programme.desc: Multiple deaths, a curse and many hauntings draw the "Most Haunted" team to the bizarre Aberglasney House in Wales.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Schooner Hotel
programme.desc: The team investigates the Schooner Inn, a 17th-century hotel with a history of murders, suicides and massacres; babies have been reportedly thrown into fires, and sixty ghosts are said to reside there.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Fitz Manor
programme.desc: Ghostly apparitions, poltergeists and secret tunnels await the "Most Haunted" team as they visit Fitz Manor, located in the heart of rural Shropshire and overlooking the River Severn.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Muckleburgh
programme.desc: The Muckleburgh Collection is said to be haunted by the museum founder and six women of the Auxiliary Territorial Service killed on that site when an anti-aircraft gun exploded. The team investigates.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark's friend Scotty wants to adopt the boy with Down's Syndrome. A custody battle occurs with the biological parents.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: For the Love of Larry
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark rescue victims trapped in a car, thanks to a helpful dog.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Another Kind of War, Another Kind of Peace

programme.sub-title: Another Kind of War, Another Kind of Peace

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: That's Our Dad
programme.desc: A children's-show host has a warm-hearted TV persona but is actually a cynic at heart.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Love at Second Sight
programme.desc: Another angel is upset that Jonathan has been assigned to find a mate for his widow.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Love and Marriage - Part 1
programme.desc: Bickering couples go on a trip to learn what it was that brought them together.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Love and Marriage - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark work to keep the three couples together.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Taryn Couper
programme.desc: Taryn Couper admits she's stuck in the 1970s so it's up to Fiona McDonald and her team of experts to turn her from Hamilton hippie to boho chic, making her look 10 years younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Lorraine Harvey
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team take on the challenge of Lorraine Harvey from Tunbridge Wells.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Under New Management
programme.desc: Victoria is a mom and apartment manager without any personal time. Her job creates a lack of structure for her to spend with her family. The Ten Years Younger team will brighten her smile, revive her appearance and open her eyes to new possibilities.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Nicki Hall
programme.desc: Nicki Hall wears her hardships on her face and she's aging quickly. But trying to dress sporty like her teenage daughters just makes her look older. This week Fiona McDonald and a team of experts help turn Nicky into the young woman she is at heart.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Unstick The 80s
programme.desc: Between her career as an attorney and raising two children, Cindi hasn't found time to update her look since the 80s. She hasn't bought an outfit since her first child was born, six years ago. The 10 Years Younger crew is ready to unleash the team.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: You Can't Outrun The Sun
programme.desc: Diana is a substitute teacher, but in her youth she was a sun-worshipper and a party girl. Those two things combined have resulted in severly damaged skin. Experts help Diana go from mousy teacher to red-hot mama, but will she look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Deconstructing Mike
programme.desc: Mike has spent a lifetime in the blazing sun and it has taken its toll. He is tired of being referred to as the "old guy" and would like to look younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Super-Mom, Super Tired
programme.desc: Three kids in three years, a career, and years of sun worshiping has left this super-mom looking less than super. After hi-tech procedures at the dermatologist, a Pilates session, new outfit and makeup, will this mom look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Estelle Bell
programme.desc: Estelle Bell is desperately in need of a confidence shake up. Can Fiona McDonald and her team of experts convince Estelle she's still young at heart and make her look 10 Years Younger in just 10 days?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Diana Turner
programme.desc: Working with men all day, Diana Turner feels more like one of the lads than one of the ladies. It's up to Fiona McDonald and the team of experts to banish Diana's tom-boy look and make her appear 10 Years Younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hip Hop Momma
programme.desc: Jessika is a working mother of two young children who's responsibilities of motherhood has left her with little time and energy for her appearance. Now she wishes she could regain some of that old sexy feeling while being a mom.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Scrubs No More
programme.desc: Darcey spends her days caring for three kids and her nights working as a nurse, with no time left for herself. Experts perform the latest procedures in dermatology and dentistry, and the glam squad takes her from scrubs to sass.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Changing For The Better
programme.desc: After Lasik to get rid of her glasses and some dermatology to give her skin a more youthful appearance, Laura gets overhauled by the Glam Squad. Now, Laura can see without her coke bottle glasses, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Crystal Clear
programme.desc: Crystal has been taking care of other people since she was eight years old; after her mother had a stroke, she cared for her younger brother. Crystal needs to focus on herself for a change. Experts do what it takes to reclaim her youthful appearance.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: It's a year since we left Leopard's Den and much has changed. The animal hospital has been rebuilt and is now up and running. It's a big day for all the family as Danny has been fighting for custody of Evan and today they will learn the judge's decision.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny and Evan's life on the run doesn't start well when Danny falls asleep at the wheel and drives into a ditch. They have to enlist a local farmer, Johann, to winch them out.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny is asked by the State Vet to help control an outbreak of rabies in the National Park. When Vanessa is concerned for the animals at Mara, Danny assures her it's a long way away and advises her to continue with business as usual.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: It's the day before Rosie's wedding. Danny is proud of his daughter and determined to feed her up now that she's eating for two. All the family are excited about the imminent return of Caroline, especially Du Plessis who can't wait to see his fiancé.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Alice and Danny are called out by a farmer who's trapped an African Wild Dog. As they're even more endangered than cheetahs and much more vicious, Danny and Alice are amazed to see one up close.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: When Du Plessis instructs the family to be around for dinner, they are intrigued to hear he's planning a big announcement. However, he won't be drawn on details and tells them to be patient.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Alice and Danny are delighted when the Animal Hospital is given responsibility for the rescue and conservation of animals in the region – it's a big achievement after all their hard work.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Alice are concerned about a missing male giraffe but Du Plessis is confident he can find him. He's as good as his word but they're upset to discover Mara lions have killed the giraffe.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper crewmen have their hands full with five badly injured patients after a car crash near Waiuku, and a massive motorcycle pile-up leaves injured bikers all over the road, and a man may have broken his neck after falling from his horse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: As a weather bomb hits, the chopper crew set out on one of the most challenging missions they have ever undertaken 20 miles off shore, a man lays face down at Muriwai beach unable to move.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: A hang glider pilot may have broken his back after a heavy crash-landing, a Manaia man is in a bad way after coming off a sea biscuit at high speed, and a crashed Waikato driver needs an urgent air-lift to hospital to save his life.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: It is the most extraordinary case diplomat Tom Walter has ever seen - 18 and 16 year-old Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson have been abandoned by their parents and left to fend for themselves.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's judgement day for abandoned Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson. After hours of questioning, Indonesian Immigration officials have confiscated the boy's passports and put them under strict house arrest.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: 59-year-old Joanne came to Thailand for a body makeover. She's had a tummy tuck and liposuction to look her best for her daughter's wedding. She loses her passport and the wound from her tummy tuck gets infected, Joanne finds herself stuck in Thailand.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Wayne has no money, no passport and a mountain of debt. Homeless and out of options, he's back at the Consulate in Bali with sobering news. But can consular officer, Tom Walter trust his story?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: 56-year-old Michael is living every parent's worst nightmare. His six-year-old son Dylan has been missing for three months now. His ex-wife didn't return him after a routine weekend visit and now he fears that she's trying to smuggle him out of Bali.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 1
programme.desc: Muriwai lifeguard's first rescue of the season is of an unexpected nature and on a remote part of the beach. Lifeguards rush to the aid of a distraught 18-year-old girl whose been sucked into a treacherous hole.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 2
programme.desc: Lifeguards struggle to keep swimmers safe as swift rips sweep them out of the flagged area. But for one boogie boarder it's too late. The young guns are put to the test as a surfer is pounded by huge swells and dragged across jagged rocks.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 3
programme.desc: It's looking like another perfect day for the mounting crowd at Muriwai Beach, but lifeguards soon have a crisis on their hands as a full scale search is mounted for a young boy.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 4
programme.desc: A surfer washes up on Muriwai Beach and lifeguards are unsure what's wrong with him. Lifeguards could be forced to shut the beach because of an invasion of a swarm of jellyfish.

programme.title: On Tour: Monster Truck Stunts
programme.desc: Today we visit the Bosslé Helldrivers and they do a gnarly stuntshow for the past forty years and I am part of it. Frightened to death but bravely part of the stunt show.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Bella Italia
programme.desc: Today in Perfect Ride: on the road in Bella Italia - the country well known for 'la dolce vita', Lamborghini, Ferrari and Mille Miglia.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Extreme Tuning

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Crazy Rides
programme.desc: The car world just gets crazier and crazier! From three-wheeled retro cars such as the Reliant Rialto, which tended to tip over at every bend? And freaky bikes with maximum speed of up to 150mph!

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Moment of Force

programme.title: Perfect Ride: To the Top!

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Tough Guys & Breathtaking Stunts

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Special Motor Show Essen

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Out of Space
programme.desc: Today's cars are out of space - vehicles that are far from the norm. The Fahrradi Farfalla is definitely one of these most unusual cars in the world. In Austria we paid its creator Hannes Langeder a visit.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Changing the Model
programme.desc: It's all about changing the model. Bigger, lighter, trendier: Audi brings the A3 Sportback to the table. On the track the Stuck brothers have got their hands on some crazy horsepower: the Mercedes C 63 AMG.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Racing Fever
programme.desc: Snow, fun and pure action in Austria! The spectacular snowmobile race is the Formula 1 of the winter. Formula 1 driver Sebastian Vettel drives at full speed in the music video of RNB star Melanie Fiona.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Wild Beasts
programme.desc: The wildest Beasts are on the loose. Today's episode is all about beastly hot cars. The latest crawler from Volkswagen is in its starting block. The VW Beetle revealingly dressed in a convertible outfit.

programme.title: Perfect Ride: Cars International
programme.desc: Whacky sleighs, supercars and stars and stripes ' the Detroit Motor Show! What's everyone been talking about in the car world? Mazda has been talking in a new language: Kodo.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Payback
programme.desc: A mysterious death by poisoning creates questions about the safety of portal technology. When a Taelon is killed in the same manner, the investigation leads to a very smart scientist that even the Resistance was scared to work with.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Friendly Fire
programme.desc: Paul Chandler plots an attack on the Taelon Embassy in DC with the ship he stole from Lili. He begs her to join him in beginning an all out war.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Heroes and Heartbreak

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Message in a Bottle
programme.desc: A Jiridian probe headed for Earth is shot down by the Taelon Embassy and crashes outside of D.C. Liam recovers the probe, but he, Augur, and Julia are captured by another underground resistance movement led by the real Colonel Liam Kincaid.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Fate Worst Than Death
programme.desc: At the bottom of a steep ravine, joggers discover a body mutilated beyond recognition. To catch a ruthless maniac, Lt. Joe Kenda must first solve the puzzle of the victim’s identity.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Murder in a Bottle
programme.desc: Eric Houston is found stabbed to death in a seedy motel, but the ensuing investigation is stymied by a long list of suspects. Lt. Joe Kenda deploys a groundbreaking new technology to catch the killer.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: My, My, Merry Christmas
programme.desc: Donald Ott is found shot to death, friends tell police he didn’t have an enemy in the world. But when Lt. Joe Kenda speaks with family, he learns of a relative who might hold the key to the mystery.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Eyes of a Child
programme.desc: A loving, churchgoing grandmother is found stabbed to death in her apartment, leaving Joe Kenda to wonder what sort of monster could do such a thing.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Sex, Lies, and Surveillance Tape
programme.desc: A confrontation between enemies turns deadly, and Lt. Joe Kenda’s best hope for answers lies with a grainy, dubbed-over surveillance tape.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: A Prayer for the Dying
programme.desc: A mother of two is found dead in the most expensive part of Colorado Springs, leaving Lt. Joe Kenda stumped—until he looks into her personal life.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Body in the Freezer
programme.desc: A meeting between two businessmen leaves one shot in the face. Things seem cut and dry until Lt. Kenda realizes the “victim” could actually be the aggressor, shot struggling over his own gun.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: River of Blood
programme.desc: Two hunters discover a blood-drenched car, its owner riddled with buckshot. Lt. Joe Kenda learns the car was reported stolen the day before, he follows its trail to a group of unlikely suspects.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Eton & Dolly, and the Pups on Parole
programme.desc: Cesar goes to jail to help wayward humans rehabilitate wayward pups through a program called "Pups on Parole."; Bulldogs learn to play fair.
programme.sub-title: Eton & Dolly, and the Pups on Parole

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Lotus Blossoms
programme.desc: A jealous dachshund learns to get along with both of his owners. Can Cesar exorcize a demon possessed German Shepherd that prevents his people from entering certain rooms of the house.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Anti-Social Sasha
programme.desc: Sasha, a pound pup, is perfect in the house, but outside she shows aggression towards other dogs. Angler, a Lab, is blind, and exhibits strange behavior around food.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Joe, and Penny, Roxy, Rico, Lou, & Solomon, and Promise
programme.desc: An Australian shepherd is so devoted to his owner that he breaks leashes to be with her; a neurotic beagle makes trouble for a pack of foster dogs; and an Italian mastiff puppy fears riding in cars.
programme.sub-title: Joe, and Penny, Roxy, Rico, Lou, & Solomon, and Promise

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer
programme.desc: Cesar explains how he reads a dog's energy and body language as he deals with two Jack Russell terriers who grew up together but fight violently.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Baby Girl
programme.desc: Suzie Dove Miles, a "cat whisperer," is set on getting a fearful Doberman mix at a shelter. Suzie has tried many of Cesar's exercises with Baby Girl, but needs Cesar’s expertise to help Baby Girl become a real dog.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Hounded By Fear
programme.desc: Melody is terrified of dogs, while pool man Tom will even leave a job site if one is near. Cesar helps them deal with their fears and anxieties.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Laxatives and Pottery/Ashes
programme.desc: Kimberly takes hundreds of laxatives a day in an attempt to lose weight. Meanwhile, Bianca prefers to eat pottery and cigarette ashes instead of food.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Wears Diapers/Eats Dryer Sheets
programme.desc: For Riley, there's nothing like the comfort of wearing a warm, wet diaper. She lives as an adult baby to escape the stresses of life. And Charmissa chews on dryer sheets for up to 10 hours a day.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Rampant Rats/Extreme Fingernails
programme.desc: Theresa has more than 60 pet hairless rats that are taking over her apartment. Jazz has been growing her fingernails for 22 years. Her longest nail is two feet long, and she calls them her children.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Gas Sniffer/Teddy Bear Obsession
programme.desc: For more than 30 years, Theresa has been addicted to smelling gasoline. Meanwhile, former drug-addict Krista has 12 'children' -- all of which are teddy bears.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 2
programme.desc: In this one-hour special, we revisit six of our addicts whose stories shocked the world. Tune in for exclusive never before seen footage in this special episode.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Drinks Nail Polish & Ear Digger
programme.desc: Bertha has been drinking up to five bottles of nail polish every day for the past five years but her family is worried she's doing permanent damage to her health. Jamie can't stop digging in her ears.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict
programme.desc: Nathaniel has been in a relationship with his car for nearly five years, taking it out on dates, buying it gifts, and even getting intimate with it. Jaye has been addicted to snorting baby powder.
programme.sub-title: Dating My Car/ Baby Powder Addict

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to My Breasts/Tape Eater
programme.desc: Sheyla has spent $250,000 on 22 breast enlargement surgeries to achieve her 38KKK bust size, despite suffering a severe infection from her recent implants. Andrea is addicted to eating adhesive tape.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Dirt/Extreme Toenails
programme.desc: Kristie has eaten dirt every day for the last 30 years, consuming more than five tons since her addiction began. Meanwhile, Ayanna is addicted to growing her toenails.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Coffee Enemas/Licks Cats
programme.desc: Trina and her husband Mike have done nearly 7,000 coffee enemas over the last two and a half years. Lisa has been addicted to licking her cat and eating clumps of its hair for three years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Extreme Hair/Addicted to Bee Stings
programme.desc: Asha hasn't cut her 21-foot long hair in nearly a quarter century and spends up to six hours a day grooming her ten-pound locks. Margaret has stung herself over 50,000 times with bees.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Inflatables/Butt Injection Addict
programme.desc: Mark has been addicted to his 15 inflatable pool toys, eating with them, sleeping with them and even bathing them. Karmello has been getting black market butt injections for the last three years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Bricks / Married To A Carnival Ride
programme.desc: For the past three years, 56-year-old Linda has been happily married to Bruce, a 70-foot carnival ride. Patrice is also happily married and showcases her addiction for eating brick.
programme.sub-title: Eats Bricks / Married To A Carnival Ride

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Being Pamela Anderson
programme.desc: Carolyn Anderson, a 29 year-old women from the UK, is addicted to transforming herself into Baywatch beauty Pamela Anderson.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Baby On Board
programme.desc: Matt and Jessica have a new baby. They want to move into a new home near the ocean around Juneau, Alaska. But waterfront homes are too expensive, so they choose a liveaboard boat!

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Isolated Village
programme.desc: Sean and Jolene want a home in the Alaskan village of Gustavus, where the wildlife runs rampant. There are no roads in or out of town and it’s so remote the bears feel free to walk into your house!

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Mrs. Alaska & Military Man
programme.desc: Pat Harrigan is a soldier, newly stationed at the army base in Fairbanks, Alaska. His wife Rocky just won the crown as the current Mrs. Alaska, but she’s a city girl at heart.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Fish Out Of Water
programme.desc: Grant and Khrissy just got engaged. He’s all-Alaskan but she’s a fish out of water from the Deep South. The couple wants to buy a house that’s a mix of the Alaskan bush and her Alabama roots.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Outhouse Life
programme.desc: Sean and Charlotte want a home in Fairbanks, Alaska, that won’t cost them a penny in utility bills. So they’re going off-the-grid. And that means one thing… there’ll be no bathrooms.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Hangar Homes
programme.desc: Born and bred Alaskans Andy and Nicole grew up in a town so remote, their family vehicles were airplanes! Now that they’re looking for a new home, they need an airplane hangar and a runway.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Remote Coves
programme.desc: Charlie and Toni are outdoor adventure junkies who want a home in Alaska that’s so remote they can catch their next meal from the ocean right off their front porch.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Homer Bound
programme.desc: Nathan and Lindsay are brand new to Alaska. They want a house similar to where Nathan’s pioneer grandfather lived, in the bayside town of Homer, surrounded by the great outdoors.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Life On A Mountain
programme.desc: Russ and Dana search for a home in the town of Girdwood, Alaska, at the base of towering Mount Alyeska. The views are spectacular, but the danger of an avalanches is real.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Guys Getaway
programme.desc: David Parks and Chris Erickson are best friends, and professional handymen. They want to buy a weekend getaway house in the wilds of Alaska, but they don’t want to spend a lot of money.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Juneau Waterfront
programme.desc: Chris and Heidi are marine adventurers who want Alaska’s marine wildlife right out their front door. They want to buy a home on the coveted waterfront of the oceanside city of Juneau.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Tiny Homes, Big Mountain
programme.desc: Pete and Martha have lived and worked in some of the wildest locations in the U.S. In Alaska they want an isolated home with views of the tallest peak in North America - Mount McKinley.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Dollars Or Drains
programme.desc: Texas native Colby wants an affordable home, but he’s in for a shock because, in Alaska, that means a dry cabin – with no running water. He doesn’t know anything about life without plumbing.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Dangerous Trails
programme.desc: Brandon and Hanna want a home on an isolated lake far into the Alaskan wild, where there’s no way in but off-roading through trails of mud or landing on water.
